To add a new game data type, start with a config file in game_engine_dev named game_config.<stem> and register the stem in the shared lists. The central registry is data_io/generater_commons.py, where get_entries() drives most downstream generators. A new row in PARSER_SPECS (in gen_data_io/generate.py) supplies the class name, struct fields, and colon-field parsing instructions. The config filename ending and PathMng getter are added via data_io/generate_path_manager.py, usually as stem + s (for example, mvt_cost -> game_config.mvt_costs). After those three registrations, run the generators in order rather than hand-editing the emitted C++.

The first step builds static holders. From gen_static_state/, run make_static_data_and_test.py with a new spec row (struct members and sample test fields). That emits static_state/<stem>_static_data.h, <stem>_static_data.cpp, and <stem>_static_key.h: typed arrays with get_item and get_item_count. The second step builds parsers. From gen_data_io/, run generate.py (or the full make_data_parser_and_test.py loop) for the new stem. That emits data_io/<stem>_parser.h/.cpp, <stem>_parser_tester.h/.cpp, and <stem>_parser_comp. Parsers use StringManager and DataParserBase to load the file, split lines, cull blanks, derive names from before the colon, and parse fields with parse_u16 and friends. If other configs may reference the new tokens, name_to_idx_callbacks.h and each parser tester pick up a <stem>_name_to_idx callback. The third step wires the bundle: run data_io/generate_path_manager.py if PathMng changed, generate_parse_manager.py for static_parsing_manager (file load, name-only parser, typed parser, getters), and generate_runtime_statics.py for runtime_statics.h/.cpp, runtime_static_loader_lib_api, runtime_static_loader_lib_comp, and the loader/statics testers. Rebuild runtime_static_loader_lib_comp to produce runtime_static_loader_lib.so.

The fourth step is validation. Build and run <stem>_parser_tester for a standalone parse of the config file. Build runtime_statics_comp and run runtime_statics_tester; ParserTestManager then writes RESULTS_NEW_<STEM> from loaded RuntimeStatics, and results_validate.py promotes that to RESULTS_VALID_<STEM>. Build runtime_static_loader_lib_comp and runtime_static_loader_comp; runtime_static_loader_tester loads the .so and checks holder counts, req bounds, maps, and effectors. At runtime the path is: config file -> PathMng -> StaticParsingManager parses into <Stem>StaticDataStruct arrays -> RuntimeStatics::load_from copies into <Stem>StaticData holders -> all of that is linked into runtime_static_loader_lib.so -> RuntimeStaticLoader loads the .so and exposes loader.statics().<stem>(). Blank separator lines in config files are dropped by cull_empty_strings everywhere, so item count is non-blank rows only.

Final testing from the data_io-folder:
./runtime_static_loader_lib_comp    # build the .so first
./runtime_static_loader_comp        # build the tester
./runtime_static_loader_tester
